# GIS Skill SDK

Build custom skills for [GIS Data Agent](https://github.com/your-org/gis-data-agent).

## Installation

```bash
pip install gis-skill-sdk
```

Or for development:

```bash
cd gis-skill-sdk
pip install -e ".[dev]"
```

## Quick Start

### Create a new skill

```bash
gis-skill new my-analysis-skill
```

This creates:
```
my-analysis-skill/
  SKILL.md          # Metadata + instructions
  references/       # Reference documents
  assets/           # Data files
```

### Edit SKILL.md

The skill file uses YAML frontmatter for metadata and Markdown for instructions:

```markdown
---
name: my-analysis-skill
description: Performs custom spatial analysis
pattern: command
trigger_keywords:
  - spatial analysis
  - my analysis
toolsets:
  - ExplorationToolset
  - GeoProcessingToolset
model_tier: standard
---

# My Analysis Skill

Detailed instructions for the LLM agent...
```

### Validate

```bash
gis-skill validate my-analysis-skill/
```

### List skills

```bash
gis-skill list /path/to/skills/
```

## Skill Patterns

| Pattern | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `command` | Direct execution of a specific task |
| `inversion` | Interview-style data gathering before analysis |
| `probe` | Exploratory analysis with hypothesis testing |
| `suggestion` | Recommends approaches based on data characteristics |
| `reactive` | Responds to events or triggers |

## API Usage

```python
from gis_skill_sdk import BaseSkill, load_skill, load_skills_directory

# Load a single skill
skill = load_skill("path/to/my-skill/")
print(skill.name, skill.metadata.pattern)

# Load all skills from a directory
skills = load_skills_directory("path/to/skills/")
for s in skills:
    print(f"{s.name}: {s.description}")

# Validate
issues = skill.validate()
if issues:
    print("Issues found:", issues)
```

